A vintage-style illustration of an old wooden sailing ship in dry dock undergoing extensive renovation, with workers on scaffolding replacing weathered planks with sleek modern metal panels. The ship is half-transformed—the stern still shows aged timber with barnacles and rope rigging, while the bow gleams with polished steel and streamlined surfaces. Warm amber workshop lighting illuminates sawdust floating in the air, contrasting with cool blue reflections off the new metallic sections. Tools both antique (hand planes, wooden mallets) and modern (welding equipment, power tools) are scattered across the dock. The scene conveys the painstaking reality of transformation—neither quick nor easy, but necessary and ongoing. Muted sepia tones blend into chrome and steel where old meets new.
